    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD represents a pinnacle of rotary engineering, preserved in showroom condition. The 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged powerplant delivers linear boost across the rev range, with recent compression tests yielding optimal results across all rotor faces. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, featuring the original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for surgical cornering precision. All vacuum lines have been refreshed to ensure flawless secondary turbo transition, and the five-speed manual gearbox offers crisp, short-throw engagement. Free of heat-cycling degradation or structural oxidation, this is a turnkey example for the discerning collector demanding mechanical purity.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
